#compdef js-yaml
# ============================================================================
# js-yaml - canonical Node YAML parser +
#            serializer's reference CLI
#            (TypeScript/Node, MIT)
#
# Author : Vladimir Zapparov + Vitaly
#           Puzrin + nodeca organization
#           (nodeca.com; Russian Node.js
#           community + library maintenance
#           organization founded by Puzrin)
# Upstream: https://github.com/nodeca/js-yaml
# npm pkg : js-yaml
#
# `js-yaml` is the canonical Node YAML
# parser library + a bundled CLI for
# converting YAML to JSON on the command
# line. The library is the de-facto
# canonical Node YAML implementation - used
# by npm CLI itself, ESLint, Prettier,
# Webpack, Babel, AVA, Mocha, Jest, and
# nearly every Node tooling that handles
# YAML config.
#
# The CLI is a thin wrapper that loads YAML
# from a file (or stdin) + emits the
# parsed result as JSON to stdout - useful
# for shell pipelines that need to query
# YAML data with jq or similar tools.
#
# Distinguishing features (library):
#   - **YAML 1.2 spec compliant** (the
#     post-Bytecode v4.x release fully
#     supports YAML 1.2; v3.x supported
#     YAML 1.1)
#   - **Safe load mode** (no arbitrary
#     code execution from untrusted YAML
#     - critical for security; many
#     legacy YAML libraries had RCE
#     vulnerabilities from custom tag
#     handling)
#   - **Pure JavaScript** (no native
#     bindings; runs in Node + browsers
#     + Deno + Bun + Cloudflare
#     Workers)
#   - **Comment-preserving load/dump**
#     (round-trip parsing + serialization
#     preserves comments via DocumentNode
#     API)
#   - **~70,000,000 weekly npm downloads**
#     (one of the highest-volume Node
#     libraries; pulled in by virtually
#     every Node web project)
#   - **6,500+ stars on github.com/
#     nodeca/js-yaml**
#
# Use cases (CLI):
#   - YAML → JSON conversion for shell
#     pipelines
#   - jq + YAML workflows (yaml | jq)
#   - YAML config validation (parse error
#     detection without semantic checks)
#   - CI/CD scripts that need YAML
#     manipulation in shell
#
# Use cases (library):
#   - Loading config files in Node apps
#     (package.yaml + lockfiles +
#     workflow files)
#   - Parsing GitHub Actions workflow
#     files (.github/workflows/*.yml)
#   - Docker Compose file manipulation
#   - Kubernetes manifest processing in
#     Node-based CRDs + operators
#   - Static-site generator config
#     (Hugo + Jekyll + 11ty front
#     matter)
#
# Usage:
#   js-yaml [-c] [-t] [file]
#   cat file.yaml | js-yaml
#
# Flags (argparse):
#   -v, --version                  - show
#                                     program's
#                                     version
#                                     number
#                                     + exit
#   -c, --compact                  - display
#                                     errors
#                                     in
#                                     compact
#                                     mode
#                                     (one
#                                     line
#                                     instead
#                                     of
#                                     multi-
#                                     line
#                                     formatted
#                                     error
#                                     output)
#   -t, --trace                    - show
#                                     stack
#                                     trace
#                                     on
#                                     error
#   -j, --to-json                  - (deprecated;
#                                     output
#                                     was
#                                     always
#                                     JSON
#                                     after
#                                     color
#                                     removal;
#                                     flag
#                                     suppressed
#                                     from
#                                     help
#                                     but
#                                     still
#                                     accepted
#                                     for
#                                     backward
#                                     compatibility)
#   -h, --help                     - show
#                                     help
#
# Positional argument:
#   [file]                         - YAML
#                                     file
#                                     to
#                                     parse
#                                     (UTF-8
#                                     encoded
#                                     without
#                                     BOM;
#                                     default
#                                     "-" =
#                                     stdin)
#
# Example invocations:
#   # Convert YAML file to JSON
#   js-yaml config.yaml
#
#   # YAML to JSON via stdin
#   cat config.yaml | js-yaml
#
#   # Pipeline with jq
#   js-yaml config.yaml | jq '.database.host'
#
#   # Pipeline from a Docker Compose file
#   cat docker-compose.yml | js-yaml | \
#     jq '.services | keys[]'
#
#   # Validate YAML syntax without
#   # processing (just check for parse
#   # errors)
#   js-yaml config.yaml > /dev/null
#
#   # Show full stack trace on error
#   js-yaml -t broken.yaml
#
#   # Compact error format for CI logs
#   js-yaml -c config.yaml || \
#     echo "YAML validation failed"
#
#   # Show version
#   js-yaml --version
#
# The js-yaml library lane IS the canonical
# Node YAML library - this CLI is the
# bundled reference utility by the same
# nodeca organization.
#
# nodeca/js-yaml is the de-facto canonical
# Node YAML library:
#   - **THE canonical Node YAML**
#     (~70,000,000 weekly npm downloads;
#     no other Node YAML library comes
#     close to this adoption volume)
#   - **YAML 1.2 spec compliant**
#     (passes the YAML test suite)
#   - **Multi-document support** (YAML
#     `---` document separators handled
#     via loadAll API)
#   - **Pluggable schema** (built-in
#     schemas: failsafe + json + core +
#     default + custom schemas with
#     Type definitions for application-
#     specific tags)
#   - **Safe vs unsafe load distinction**
#     (load() = safe by default; older
#     loadSafe()/load() distinction
#     simplified in v4.x to just load())
#   - **Browser-compatible** (the same
#     library runs unmodified in
#     browsers; many web tools use it
#     for client-side YAML editing)
#
